In this statement, President Obama expresses his condolences to the family of King Abdullah bin Abdulaziz and the people of Saudi Arabia upon his death. He acknowledges King Abdullah's contributions to Saudi Arabia and the Arab world, particularly his efforts in advancing the Arab Peace Initiative. The President also highlights King Abdullah's dedication to education and engagement with the world. He emphasizes the importance of the U.S.-Saudi relationship and values their friendship. The statement concludes with a prayer for peace for King Abdullah.